title: The Exploration Company claims partial success of Mission Possible reentry spacecraft
summary: The Exploration Company reported partial success in its Mission Possible test flight of a reentry capsule, which was lost before splashdown. The mission carried payloads from various customers and was part of SpaceX's Transporter-14 rideshare. ICEYE is mentioned as one of the companies with satellites on the same launch but is not directly involved in any deal described in the article.
